  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "8. the king arose, and sat in the gate—He appeared daily in the usual place for the hearing of causes.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "all the people came before the king—that is, the loyal natives who had been faithful to his government, and fought in his cause.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Israel had fled—that is, the adherents of Absalom, who, on his defeat, had dispersed and saved themselves by flight.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
