  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Than the king arose, and sat in the gate,.... Of the city, a public place, where the inhabitants met on divers accounts at times, and where there were always people passing and repassing: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and they told unto all the people; or it was reported to the soldiers particularly: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "saying, behold the king doth sit in the gate; has laid aside his mourning, appears in public, and receives his friends, and attends to business: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and all the people came before the king; to congratulate him on the victory obtained, to receive his thanks and his favours: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for Israel had fled every man to his tent: or to his city, as the Targum; that is, those that followed Absalom; which is observed not on account of what goes before, but of what follows after; see 2 Samuel 18:17. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "for Israel had fled every man to his tent: or to his city, as the Targum; that is, those that followed Absalom; which is observed not on account of what goes before, but of what follows after; see ",
            "children": []
          },
